<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 8:36PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
southeastern Roanoke, Bedford, southeastern Botetourt and
northeastern Franklin Counties through 915 PM EDT...
At 836 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Blue Ridge to near Stewartsville to near
Boones Mill. Movement was east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Vinton...
Bedford...
Buchanan...
Troutville...
Boones Mill...
Stewartsville...
and Huddleston.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
